        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2711441525" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8968827443092904114"><b>A group read with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/68070948-elena' rel='nofollow noopener'>Elena</a>. Sadly we lost everybody else along the road.</b><br/><br/>Book 7 begins right where book 6 left. Merlin was trying to escape from his place of imprisonment. It turns out given enough time everything is possible. <br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1550196064i/27067032._SX540_.jpg' alt='Escape' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Unfortunately in his case it appears he escaped from proverbial frying pan into the fire. Several people/groups made it their priority to rid the world off poor guy who strictly speaking did not do anything to deserve such attention. To make matters worse, Merlin began to susp</span>
  <span id="freeText8968827443092904114" style="display:none"><b>A group read with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/68070948-elena" rel="nofollow noopener">Elena</a>. Sadly we lost everybody else along the road.</b><br><br>Book 7 begins right where book 6 left. Merlin was trying to escape from his place of imprisonment. It turns out given enough time everything is possible. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1550196064i/27067032._SX540_.jpg" alt="Escape" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Unfortunately in his case it appears he escaped from proverbial frying pan into the fire. Several people/groups made it their priority to rid the world off poor guy who strictly speaking did not do anything to deserve such attention. To make matters worse, Merlin began to suspect for some parties he was only a minor inconvenience to be swept aside on their way to destruction of Amber itself. And the guy loved that place (who does not; I do). So Merlin was trying to stay alive wondering who honored him with such attention - can we say he was overloaded with it? <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1550196352i/27067036.jpg" alt="Overload" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>As it might already be obvious the action in the book was practically non-stop. Still we have time to get to know one of royal sisters of Amber better (Flora). She appeared to be more than just drop-dead (in her case people actually did) gorgeous face and a fascinating character on her own. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1550196616i/27067042._SY540_.jpg" width="184" height="259" alt="Flora" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>I love some of the things she carries in her purse - they show she knows our world very well indeed. Speaking about the royal siblings their number changed yet again, but I am not going to spoil it. <br><br>Some interesting glimpses at both Amber and Courts of Chaos are given adding to the overall world building. The latter is very unique, unmatched, and intriguing by the way. <br><br>The ending was bizarre enough to warrant diving into the next book right away. Unfortunately I have to exercise self-discipline and wait for a month to proceed. <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1550196942i/27067047._SX540_.jpg" alt="Self-control" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Oh well, life in not always fair. 5 stars is the final rating. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8968827443092904114" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

