        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer577752533" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8408635138245193769">Well, that took forever.<br/>Merlin is boring. His life is boring; his problems are boring. And now he&apos;s in Wonderland. WTF Zelazny? How&apos;s the LSD?<br/><br/>Seriously. I will keep reading the series, because potential. And completion. But I miss Corwin I think more than Merlin does. I like the potential of sorcery, but I really think this thing is being dragged out for no damn reason. Why were the first five books so much more engaging and fantastical? Even the 900th trip through Shadow held my interest better</span>
  <span id="freeText8408635138245193769" style="display:none">Well, that took forever.<br />Merlin is boring. His life is boring; his problems are boring. And now he's in Wonderland. WTF Zelazny? How's the LSD?<br /><br />Seriously. I will keep reading the series, because potential. And completion. But I miss Corwin I think more than Merlin does. I like the potential of sorcery, but I really think this thing is being dragged out for no damn reason. Why were the first five books so much more engaging and fantastical? Even the 900th trip through Shadow held my interest better than this.<br /><br />Well, not everything can be perfect. Carry on.</span>
