<div id="review_135355047" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/135355047" />
    <a title="Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2153253-michael"><img alt="Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1582796315p2/2153253.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/135355047?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael" href="/user/show/2153253-michael">Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780783892948" href="/book/show/1392997.Blood_of_Amber">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2153253-michael?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2153253-michael?shelf=2010">2010</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer135355047" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2084454937635508253">Book 7 of 10 of the <i>Amber Chronicles</i>. These books just keep getting better. The story structure is much better in books 6 and 7 than the previous installments. It seems that Zelazny finally got in the zone. Lots of mystery in the last two and it leaves questions unanswered at the end. Fortunately, I don&apos;t have to wait in order to read the next one. <br/><br/>One thing I am concerned about are the endings. They just don&apos;t quite satisfy. Book 5 in the series was the end of Corwin as the protagonist in the f</span>
  <span id="freeText2084454937635508253" style="display:none">Book 7 of 10 of the <i>Amber Chronicles</i>. These books just keep getting better. The story structure is much better in books 6 and 7 than the previous installments. It seems that Zelazny finally got in the zone. Lots of mystery in the last two and it leaves questions unanswered at the end. Fortunately, I don't have to wait in order to read the next one. <br /><br />One thing I am concerned about are the endings. They just don't quite satisfy. Book 5 in the series was the end of Corwin as the protagonist in the first five books in the series, and I can't say I was completely satisfied with that ending. It did wrap things up sufficiently, but left me still wanting. I'm hoping I continue to enjoy these last 3 books in the series, and there is no reason to think that I won't. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2084454937635508253" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


